Florida is going to launch a strategic Bitcoin reserve, and here’s how we’re going to do it 👇

Florida has a very good chance of creating a strategic Bitcoin reserve this session, which starts in Q1 of 2025.

Here’s what you need to know:

The Speaker of the Florida House, Danny Perez, and the President of the Senate, Ben Albritton, both helped push our Anti-CBDC Bill in Florida.

Both leaders are very pro-Bitcoin, especially Speaker Perez, who understands the technology very well.

And of course, with Ron DeSantis as one of the most pro-Bitcoin governors in the United States, things are looking pretty good.

Here are some of the ways we can implement a Strategic Bitcoin Reserve in Florida:

1) Leverage our $185.7B pension fund (4th largest in the U.S.) to allocate a small percentage to Bitcoin as a hedge against inflation.

To be clear, Florida has already invested in Bitcoin and crypto-related assets through our pension fund.

The pension allocates its funds to hedge funds, and some of those hedge funds have bought various stocks in the Bitcoin space (miners, MSTR, Coinbase as examples) while also buying liquid tokens.

Just investing ONE percent of our pension fund into Bitcoin would be $1.857 billion.

2) Use our budget surplus ($116.5B FY 2024-25) to responsibly invest in BTC without cutting essential services.

Florida often has a budget surplus because we are kick-ass and have a very well-run state (unlike the rest of you 😉).

But inflation and time will eat away at any budget surpluses we have. Investing just ONE percent of our surplus would be $1.165 billion.

My organization will be pushing this hard, along with about three other pro-Bitcoin bills this legislative session.

Stay tuned!

🤔 Blockchain vs. Bitcoin: What’s the Difference?

It’s common to hear blockchain and Bitcoin used interchangeably, but they’re not the same. Let’s break it down:

🔹 Blockchain is the technology that powers Bitcoin, providing a decentralized and secure way to record and verify data. It’s versatile, with applications across industries far beyond cryptocurrency.

🔸 Bitcoin is a cryptocurrency built on blockchain, designed for decentralized, peer-to-peer digital transactions.

🟡 Bitcoin is digital gold 
Ⓜ️ Litecoin is digital silver 

🟡 Digital gold is better than physical gold.
Ⓜ️ Digital silver better than physical silver

Ⓜ️#Litecoin (LTC) distinguishes itself from both #Bitcoin (BTC) and #Ethereum (ETH) through several key advantages that make it a superior choice for certain applications :

🔷 Litecoin offers faster transaction times with block generation occurring approximately every 2.5 minutes, compared to Bitcoin's 10 minutes, enabling quicker confirmations for transactions. This speed is particularly beneficial for merchants and users looking for efficient payment solutions

🔷 Litecoin typically has lower transaction fees than both Bitcoin and Ethereum, making it more economical for microtransactions and daily use. The use of the Scrypt hashing algorithm in Litecoin's mining process also broadens accessibility, allowing for mining with less specialized hardware compared to Bitcoin's SHA-256, which is predominantly mined by ASICs. 

🔷 Litecoin has served as a testing ground for Bitcoin improvements, such as Segregated Witness (SegWit), ensuring that the network can adopt new technologies with less risk

🔷 Litecoin's total supply cap is set at 84 million coins, four times that of Bitcoin, potentially making it more accessible for widespread adoption. These factors collectively position Litecoin as a more practical cryptocurrency for everyday transactions and a complement to Bitcoin's store-of-value role, while offering a simpler, less gas-intensive alternative to Ethereum's smart contract platform.

Ⓜ️#Litecoin ( $LTC) of the people, by the people and for the people.🤝🤝🚀🚀

#Litecoin $LTC  #ETH #BTC

cleaned_data.original_text:
It's crazy that there are people on this app who still insist that Bitcoin isn't money, that it's no good as a medium of exchange, that no one is spending it, that it has no use case, etc., etc., etc.

And yet...

Half a world away from home, across the ocean, there's this farmer's market in Uvita, Costa Rica, home to @BitcoinJungleCR.

I've never been here, I don't speak the language, I don't know any of these people, they don't know me. They have no reason to trust me any more than any other stranger.

I'm just passing through.

And yet, I could buy just about anything and everything I needed with (you guessed it) ... Bitcoin.

And no one was surprised when I asked to pay with Bitcoin. Almost as if, you know, it's just another way of paying for stuff, almost as if, you know, it's just money.

There's three takeaways here:

1. 
More and more people will continue to adopt Bitcoin. Precisely because it is so useful as a global, neutral, internet-native money. 

2.
Guiding, helping and educating them, the way @BitcoinJungleCR is doing, speeds up the process and ultimately benefits us all in building a better world.

3.
Most of those who are familiar with Bitcoin, yet refuse to acknowledge that it is a useful form of money, will likely continue to ignore any and all evidence to the contrary. If they haven't seen it by now, there's no point trying to convince them. They probably don't need it. Best we focus our energy on those who do need it, and leave the stubborn deniers to themselves.

Strive's first of many planned Bitcoin solutions will democratize access to Bitcoin bonds, which are bonds issued by corporations to purchase Bitcoin. We believe these bonds provide attractive risk-return exposure to Bitcoin, yet they are not available to be purchased by most investors.

Since our inception, Strive has called out the long-term investment risks caused by the global fiat debt crisis, inflation, and geopolitical tensions. We strongly believe there is no better long-term investment to hedge against these risks than thoughtful exposure to Bitcoin.

We believe that both everyday Americans and institutional investors should have a meaningful core allocation to the Bitcoin economy in their portfolios. That includes directly owning Bitcoin, allocating to Bitcoin bonds, and investing in Bitcoin-focused companies.

#Bitcoin 2021 senesi boğa zamanı ilk sıçramasını yaptıktan sonra günlükte EMA50 seviyesine kadar geri çekilme yaşamış ve sonra 50 günlük ortalama seviyesinden 2x ten fazla yükseliş yaşayarak ATH yapmıştı ve bu ATH koşusu yaklaşık 9 ay sürmüştü.

Şimdi yine benzeri bir durum yaşanıyor. $BTC , ilk sıçramasından sonra, $92.5k da günlükte EMA50 seviyesine temas edip dönüş yaşadı. Şimdi cycle tekrar ederse - ki bu zamana kadar hep etti - bitcoin 2 ileri 1 geri $160k üzerine atacaktır. Mayıs satışı öncesi ATH olur ama bir tur daha ATH için Eylül - Ekim gibi deneme yapar gibi.

Unutmayalım; uzun vadede günlükte EMA50 seviyesi yükselen trenddeki bir varlık için trendin devamının korunması için çok önemlidir.

Every four years, a visionary leader emerges in the crypto space—someone extraordinary who unites communities and leads them into a new era of growth and innovation. These leaders bring something special, something unique that captures hearts and onboard new waves of people into the world of crypto.

In 2021, it was Ryoshi with Shib. He had a vision, and from that vision, Shib was born—a project that became a movement.

Today, I feel that same spark of inspiration, that same sense of destiny, with Ron and $UFD. Every great community needs a great leader, and my conviction in this meme coin couldn’t be stronger.

The future is bright, and I’m all in. Until then, wishing everyone a fantastic New Year
